&quot;Edna Wallace Hopper (January 17, 1872 - December 14, 1959) was an American actress on stage and in silent films.&quot;
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edna_Wallace_Hopper" rel="nofollow">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edna_Wallace_Hopper</a>

In June 1916, she was co-star in the movie &quot;The Perils of Divorce&quot;, see the review in the <a href="http://chroniclingamerica.loc.gov/lccn/sn85042242/1916-07-14/ed-1/seq-4/" rel="nofollow">Bismarck daily tribune., July 14, 1916, Image 4</a>, column 2 with photo of her and Frank Sheridan. Obviously, divorce was considered in those days as the greatest evil and it was not unusual for a man to divorce his wife if he saw another man kissing her hand ...
